"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(client.client_id) AS male_client_count\nFROM client\nJOIN disp ON client.client_id = disp.client_id\nJOIN account ON disp.account_id = account.account_id\nJOIN district ON account.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE client.gender = 'M'\nAND district.district_id = (\n    SELECT district.district_id\n    FROM district\n    ORDER BY A15 DESC\n    LIMIT 1 OFFSET 1\n);\n``` \n\nThis SQL query counts the number of male clients in the branch where the second-highest number of crimes were committed in 1995. It uses joins to connect the relevant tables and a subquery to find the district with the second-highest crime count."